in, and then sprinkle the water f=\r\nrom the kalasha on the yajamana and the cotton thread. The cotton thread is=\r\n then worn on the wrist (right hand for men, left hand for women) as an amu=\r\nlet, and the vibhuti is worn on the forehead.\n&gt; \n&gt; The vaidika procedure sp=\r\necifies particular sets of mantras. In the bodhayana tradition, this starts=\r\n with the rAkshoghnam (something to destroy rAkshasas). However, you may us=\r\ne some other mantra in it&#39;s place. If you are using the hanuman chalisa, as=\r\n Narasimha suggested, you can chant that mantra a number of times, and then=\r\n wear the thread and vibhuti. Or, you could follow the Satayanarayana puja =\r\nmanual with the cotton thread and vibhuti near by, and then sprinkle the th=\r\nread with water and then wear it and the vibhuti. You could even put a pot =\r\nof water, think of Varuna, then do a bunch of bhajans, and then wear the th=\r\nread and sprinkle the water on the area where you will be sleeping. The pri=\r\nnciple is the same. \n&gt; \n&gt; The procedure for &quot;pratisarabandha&quot; specifically =\r\nmentions disturbed sleep as an application.\n&gt; \n&gt; sasneham,\n&gt; \n&gt;     ajit\n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; On Mon, Aug 5, 2013 at 8:20 AM, ilya.suzdalnitski &lt;ilya.suzdalnitski@=\r\nyahoo.com&gt; wrote:\n&gt; Hello everyone,\n&gt; \n&gt; Recently I was staying at an old h=\r\nouse in a village. I had trouble falling asleep, because I could hear stran=\r\nge noises -  creaking and something moving in the attic. I&#39;m very sensitive=\r\n to different energies - I don&#39;t see anything, but I feel whether something=\r\n divine or rather evil is present in a certain place. That place didn&#39;t fee=\r\nl good to me.\n&gt; \n&gt; I was staying there for 10 days and every night I would =\r\nmake up because of a feeling of somebody staring at me - I could see them b=\r\nut once I started focusing on them, they vanished. Sometimes I would wake u=\r\np in a terrified state bre